{"parentUuid":"4fcdbe59-9133-468c-98fd-6f283ffcbf4a","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/bhyslop/projects/rbm_alpha_recipemuster","sessionId":"fce9149c-83d6-4310-bee9-8d33afe613a9","version":"2.1.39","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a4e5b9b","slug":"tingly-knitting-bunny","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_018atNctTXs89J5V6T1QJypj","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→//axhrb_regime\n     2→{rbrv_regime}\n     3→\n     4→This regime specifies variables that define container vessel configurations within the Recipe Bottle system.\n     5→Each\n     6→{rbrv_regime}\n     7→instance represents a vessel image source, either bound from an external registry or conjured from a Dockerfile.\n     8→RBRV assignment files are found in `rbev-vessels/*/rbrv.env` and configure image sourcing for bottle deployments.\n     9→\n    10→//axhrv_variable\n    11→{rbrv_sigil}\n    12→\n    13→Unique identifier for the vessel.\n    14→Must be 1-64 characters forming a valid cross-context identifier.\n    15→Must match the vessel directory name.\n    16→\n    17→//axhrv_variable\n    18→{rbrv_description}\n    19→\n    20→Human-readable description of the vessel purpose.\n    21→Optional; 0-512 characters.\n    22→\n    23→//axhrv_variable\n    24→{rbrv_vessel_mode}\n    25→\n    26→Selects vessel provisioning strategy.\n    27→Must be\n    28→{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind}\n    29→or\n    30→{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}.\n    31→\n    32→//axhrgb_group\n    33→{rbrv_group_binding}\n    34→\n    35→//axhrgc_gate\n    36→{rbrv_vessel_mode}\n    37→{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind}\n    38→\n    39→Variables in this group apply only when\n    40→{rbrv_vessel_mode}\n    41→is\n    42→{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind}.\n    43→Binding retrieves a pre-built image from an external registry without local build steps.\n    44→\n    45→//axhrgv_variable\n    46→{rbrv_bind_image}\n    47→\n    48→Fully-qualified image reference to copy from an external registry.\n    49→Must be a valid FQIN; 1-512 characters.\n    50→\n    51→//axhrgb_group\n    52→{rbrv_group_conjuring}\n    53→\n    54→//axhrgc_gate\n    55→{rbrv_vessel_mode}\n    56→{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}\n    57→\n    58→Variables in this group apply only when\n    59→{rbrv_vessel_mode}\n    60→is\n    61→{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}.\n    62→Conjuring builds a vessel image locally from a Dockerfile and build context in the repository.\n    63→\n    64→//axhrgv_variable\n    65→{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile}\n    66→\n    67→Path to Dockerfile relative to repository root.\n    68→Must be 1-512 characters.\n    69→\n    70→//axhrgv_variable\n    71→{rbrv_conjure_bldcontext}\n    72→\n    73→Build context path relative to repository root.\n    74→Must be 1-512 characters.\n    75→\n    76→//axhrgv_variable\n    77→{rbrv_conjure_platforms}\n    78→\n    79→Space-separated list of target platforms for multi-platform builds.\n    80→Must be 1-512 characters.\n    81→Examples: `linux/amd64`, `linux/amd64 linux/arm64`.\n    82→\n    83→//axhrgv_variable\n    84→{rbrv_conjure_binfmt_policy}\n    85→\n    86→Controls whether cross-platform emulation via binfmt is permitted during builds.\n    87→Must be\n    88→{rbrv_binfmt_allow}\n    89→or\n    90→{rbrv_binfmt_forbid}.\n    91→"}]},"uuid":"46865dc3-43eb-4c26-8742-74629756f688","timestamp":"2026-02-12T16:25:25.139Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"4fcdbe59-9133-468c-98fd-6f283ffcbf4a"}
